60%);','width: calc(40%);','width: calc(40%);','width: calc(20%);',NULL,'2023-10-01 04:35:42'),(130,'Scotch Old Fashioned','SCOTCH WHISKY','https://cocktailclub.com/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcocktailclub.fra1.digitaloceanspaces.com%2F3283e43cfa9c86f79b621a1a1a032d06c0f7c8590f23304dec2b6bd297fcf4fc%3F&w=3840&q=75','Presenting the most iconic Scotch cocktail in history: The Old Fashioned. Originally believed to have been created at the Pendennis Club in Louisville, the Old Fashioned cocktail has appeared in a long list of songs, movies, and books over the years due to its iconic status.','width: calc(100%);','width: calc(60%);','width: calc(40%);','width: calc(80%);',NULL,'2023-10-01 04:35:42'),(131,'Pink Gin Spritz','PINK GIN','https://cocktailclub.com/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcocktailclub.fra1.digitaloceanspaces.com%2Ff3ae56d9d5e7f083cdebf21de6b282e84da014c7108429c160154ed57f004ff5%3F&w=3840&q=75','This Pink Gin cocktail is a delicious strawberry take on the classic spritz. Looks good, tastes better.','width: calc(40%);','width: calc(40%);','width: calc(40%);','width: calc(40%);',NULL,'2023-10-01 04:35:42'),(132,'Original Piña Colada','COCONUT RUM','https://cocktailclub.com/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcocktailclub.fra1.digitaloceanspaces.com%2F7e494702b21d520810a8009e6cdfa3e47505898ff6a1f05e810e6527e0d3a18b%3F&w=3840&q=75','One of the world’s most popular summer cocktails, the Piña Colada tastes refreshing and sweet. It´s super easy to make and perfect to enjoy with friends. It’s no surprise why it’s a favorite in beach bars everywhere! Created in the 20th Century, it has been enjoyed on holidays and poolsides ever since.','width: calc(40%);','width: calc(80%);','width: calc(40%);','width: calc(0%);',NULL,'2023-10-01 04:35:42'),(133,'Espresso Martini (Low Sugar)','VODKA','https://cocktailclub.com/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcocktailclub.fra1.digitaloceanspaces.com%2F09bc8374c09f1d1978623fdfabdd73b9bc6aae6fe3409a1cdc75e67ef1b4c28a%3F&w=3840&q=75','The famous Espresso Martini is a top drink and a classic Kahlúa cocktail. Legend says that the famous late bartender legend Dick Bradsell invented the Espresso Martini in his London Bar in 1983 when a British supermodel walked up to him and gave him this peculiar request: “Can you please make something that will wake me up and then f**k me up?”','width: calc(80%);','width: calc(40%);','width: calc(20%);','width: calc(40%);',NULL,'2023-10-01 04:35:42'),(134,'London Gin & Tonic','GIN','https://cocktailclub.com/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcocktailclub.fra1.digitaloceanspaces.com%2Fe47a345b10076abeca16fed6127ec80d447c7e3fbeb26fe647f0236de45e9497%3F&w=3840&q=75','Don’t fuss over it, drink it.','width: calc(60%);','width: calc(40%);','width: calc(40%);','width: calc(60%);',NULL,'2023-10-01 04:35:42'),(135,'Lillet Vive','APERITIVO LIQUEUR','https://cocktailclub.com/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcocktailclub.fra1.digitaloceanspaces.com%2Fd7cc3420af91d5b6c24bc4787a1eb097c0236f7396788cedf7af823e836bfa9e%3F&w=3840&q=75','Thirst quenching, refreshing and low in alcohol, a great cocktail for a summer’s afternoon or even as an apéritif before lunch! In French, the word “Vive” means live or long life, so Lillet Vive means Lillet Life while Vive L’apéritif translates as long live the apéritif. There are only 105 calories in one serving of Lillet Vive.','width: calc(60%);','width: calc(40%);','width: calc(20%);','width: calc(40%);',NULL,'2023-10-01 04:35:42'),(136,'Original Cuban Daiquiri','RUM','https://cocktailclub.com/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcocktailclub.fra1.digitaloceanspaces.com%2F08c9c90d008a1ccf1189807d459af75871270248ff65258bcbab7a41e5effb60%3F&w=3840&q=75','The ultimate Cuban classic! The name of the Daiquiri itself is said to have originated in Cuba around 1900, where there is a small town outside Santiago of the same name.','width: calc(60%);','width: calc(60%);','width: calc(80%);','width: calc(40%);',NULL,'2023-10-01 04:35:42'),(137,'Especial Cuba Libre','RUM','https://cocktailclub.com/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcocktailclub.fra1.digitaloceanspaces.com%2F3b654f16aeb5733672259caf61e87513aaec11d86135d7e017b61efdfc41a4fb%3F&w=3840&q=75','A timeless classic, and simply delicious! Not to be confused with a basic rum and cola, the authentic Cuba Libre needs a generous squeeze of lime to even out the drink’s sweetness. An aged golden rum with hints of vanilla and caramel takes this simple, sociable cocktail to the next level.','width: calc(40%);','width: calc(60%);','width: calc(40%);','width: calc(20%);',NULL,'2023-10-01 04:35:42'),(138,'The Old Cuban','RUM','https://cocktailclub.com/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcocktailclub.fra1.digitaloceanspaces.com%2F729b1d1555b3b81b2b497a6adcae8819ed18d1812d0d9daff993d7fa6034ed5c%3F&w=3840&q=75','The Old Cuban was invented by Saunders in 2001, and quickly made its way into bar books across America. Like all great classic cocktails, the recipe is deceptively simple, requiring just rum, sparkling wine, lime, mint and bitters.','width: calc(60%);','width: calc(60%);','width: calc(60%);','width: calc(40%);',NULL,'2023-10-01 04:35:42'),(139,'JungleBird','DARK RUM','https://cocktailclub.com/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcocktailclub.fra1.digitaloceanspaces.com%2F1276f0f17c157cc2bd41192fe08df301d49d47b3d559d374c817dc7bd7d33da8%3F&w=3840&q=75','According to the first traceable Jungle Bird cocktail recipe in “The New American Bartender’s Guide” by John J. Poister in 1989, it was created in 1978 in the former KL Hilton’s Aviary Bar on Jalan Sultan Ismail.','width: calc(60%);','width: calc(60%);','width: calc(60%);','width: calc(40%);',NULL,'2023-10-01 04:35:42'),(140,'Original Cuban Mojito','RUM','https://cocktailclub.com/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcocktailclub.fra1.digitaloceanspaces.com%2Ff5b7fc21e22d468e23542dba6a8eca493c0dcc07789bc344f52547d25256f2ea%3F&w=3840&q=75','A true taste of Cuba! Enjoy the sensorial experience of making an authentic Cuban Mojito at home by following our simple “Mix, Muddle, Mix” recipe. Be sure to make enough to share with your friends!','width: calc(60%);','width: calc(40%);','width: calc(80%);','width: calc(40%);',NULL,'2023-10-01 04:35:42'),(141,'Rue no.9','GIN','https://cocktailclub.com/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcocktailclub.fra1.digitaloceanspaces.com%2F2c0742a6f81ed3e17c0234455dc11aaad1823ac629a82fff50242cea90e55f2a%3F&w=3840&q=75','Created by Alex Kratena, 2019. RUE N ° 9 comes from the Ruta Chalepensis plant, grown in tropical Africa and more specifically in Ethiopia where it’s used as a herb or medicinal plant.','width: calc(80%);','width: calc(60%);','width: calc(40%);','width: calc(40%);',NULL,'2023-10-01 04:35:42'),(142,'Jacques Rose','CALVADOS','https://cocktailclub.com/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcocktailclub.fra1.digitaloceanspaces.com%2F8d0f7e19c84cc328eb9f1949f67c27eb386bc61e4a87a8829557593cfffefdf6%3F&w=3840&q=75','Crisp, tart, and fruity – the real description of this cocktail, grenadine, and lemon in their perfect balance between acid and sweet enhance all the aromas in this cocktail.','width: calc(60%);','width: calc(60%);','width: calc(60%);','width: calc(40%);',NULL,'2023-10-01 04:35:42'),(143,'Whisky Highball','SCOTCH WHISKY','https://cocktailclub.com/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcocktailclub.fra1.digitaloceanspaces.com%2F0ff9b8a5af1e376d2373e5557fd53a35a2a739007a94b79d494b4a8f54b6bf2d%3F&w=3840&q=75','Initially, the most common highball was made with Scotch whisky and carbonated water, known simply as a ‘Scotch and soda’. … New York barman Patrick Duffy claimed the highball was brought to the U.S. in 1894 from England by actor E. J. Ratcliffe.','width: calc(80%);','width: calc(0%);','width: calc(20%);','width: calc(20%);',NULL,'2023-10-01 04:35:42'),(144,'The Cuban # 2','LIGHT RUM','https://cocktailclub.com/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcocktailclub.fra1.digitaloceanspaces.com%2Ffcdb6319e5816c6005004ccf7ed83724c532e554a5b59f63e17b0054be54c512%3F&w=3840&q=75','The Cuban #2 (also called The Bacardi Cocktail) was created sometime around 1917 in Cuba. There are two different ideas about this drink and its ingredients. The first is that this drink originally DID NOT contain any Grenadine and was simply a Daiquiri made with Bacardi. The Grenadine was said to have been added sometime during prohibition when it emerged in New York City. Some people say that the Grenadine has always been in the drink from its inception','width: calc(60%);','width: calc(40%);','width: calc(60%);','width: calc(20%);',NULL,'2023-10-01 04:35:42'),(145,'Flying Dutchman','GENEVER','https://cocktailclub.com/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcocktailclub.fra1.digitaloceanspaces.com%2F69a75ff03630121fc11f6004454dbf4f7a9eee5530669ee9e69a941a7612e332%3F&w=3840&q=75','A simple recipe created to reflect the view that the Netherlands has on cocktails in a bar, Dutch drinking culture ingredients. Genever is an old way of mixing aged malt spirit and botanical flavors like gin.','width: calc(100%);','width: calc(20%);','width: calc(0%);','width: calc(60%);',NULL,'2023-10-01 04:35:42'),(146,'Red Snapper','GIN','https://cocktailclub.com/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcocktailclub.fra1.digitaloceanspaces.com%2Fe861e44f2b586223646389c6b345f22a24885a612fbe62ac639f4bd935edca73%3F&w=3840&q=75','It started as a Bloody Mary, with references to it first being served in 1934 at the St. Regis hotel in New York by Fernand Petiot who brought the recipe with him from Paris (where some accounts claim he invented it). Since the name “Bloody Mary” was deemed to be a little too vulgar for the establishment, it was re-christened the “Red Snapper” It is also said that since vodka wasn’t yet easily available in the US, gin was used instead. Eventually, the original name was returned to the drink, but','width: calc(40%);','width: calc(0%);','width: calc(40%);','width: calc(20%);',NULL,'2023-10-01 04:35:42'),(147,'Horse\'s Neck','BOURBON','https://cocktailclub.com/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcocktailclub.fra1.digitaloceanspaces.com%2Fb518895b04b830225804065d02c0ff6c21dfd008899bbf6748967ceaf4b9e738%3F&w=3840&q=75','This is an old drink that dates back to the 1800s. Its origins were as a virgin drink (lemon peel and ginger ale), but later, booze was added to it and its full name was a Horse’s Neck with a Kick. The kick was Brandy or bourbon and Bitters','width: calc(60%);','width: calc(40%);','width: calc(40%);','width: calc(40%);',NULL,'2023-10-01 04:35:42'),(148,'Wakame Gin','GIN','https://cocktailclub.com/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcocktailclub.fra1.digitaloceanspaces.com%2F776e1030125eb04d41dae87ece3c39c3dd8c41b01ab99f10a88e9ba0777003de%3F&w=3840&q=75','Inspired by the Ocean Bottle project and its devotion to the welfare of our oceans, we managed to revert the idea of the penicillin cocktail, taking its main flavors of the sea; smoked, salt, gin, and ginger. to achieve a perfect balance in a new, refreshing cocktail with a certain complexity.','width: calc(60%);','width: calc(40%);','width: calc(40%);','width: calc(40%);',NULL,'2023-10-01 04:35:42'),(149,'Maid in Cuba Bacardi','ABSINTHE','https://cocktailclub.com/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcocktailclub.fra1.digitaloceanspaces.com%2F029a8f47adb8921f5698f2af83299ee593e777e2faa4e2d320349b36e946f6b4%3F&w=3840&q=75','내용없음','width: calc(60%);','width: calc(60%);','width: calc(60%);','width: calc(20%);',NULL,'2023-10-01 04:35:42'),(150,'Meirgroni','AQUAVIT','https://cocktailclub.com/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcocktailclub.fra1.digitaloceanspaces.com%2F62176ba19ba477e7fc4402dffe419701bb3658a64aa30b303a1a699a9c820be1%3F&w=3840&q=75','A delicious twist to the classic Negroni…just 3 equal measures, stirred in your glass! Strong, bitter, and punchy.','width: calc(100%);','width: calc(60%);','width: calc(40%);','width: calc(100%);',NULL,'2023-10-01 04:35:42'),(151,'Espresso Martini Grey Goose','GREY GOOSE VODKA','https://cocktailclub.com/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcocktailclub.fra1.digitaloceanspaces.com%2Ff6c198df5e96c9b7c46596eaa06f81e